Name: Mouse
Summary: Used to receive input from the user. Actually tracks mouse events and keyboard events.

Members.Name: Hit
Members.Summary: The CoordinateFrame of where the Mouse ray is currently hitting a 3D object in the Workspace.  If the mouse is not over any 3D objects in the Workspace, this property is nil.

Members.Name: Icon
Members.Summary: The current Texture of the Mouse Icon. Stored as a string, for more information on how to format the string go here

Members.Name: Origin

Members.Summary: The CoordinateFrame of where the Mouse is when the mouse is not clicking.  This CoordinateFrame will be very close to the Camera.CoordinateFrame.

Members.Summary: The Part the mouse is currently over. If the mouse is not currently over any object (on the skybox, for example) this property is nil.

Members.Name: TargetFilter
Members.Summary: A Part or Model that the Mouse will ignore when trying to find the Target, TargetSurface and Hit.

Members.Name: TargetSurface
Members.Summary: The NormalId (Top, Left, Down, etc.) of the face of the part the Mouse is currently over.

Members.Name: UnitRay
Members.Summary: The Unit Ray from where the mouse is (Origin) to the current Mouse.Target.

Name: FlangeSoundEffect

Summary: A Reverb audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

Name: EqualizerSoundEffect

Name: CompressorSoundEffect
Summary: A Compressor audio effect that can be applied to a Sound or SoundGroup.

Members.Name: AmbientReverb
Members.Summary: The ambient sound environment.  May not work when using hardware sound

Members.Name: DopplerScale
Members.Summary: The doppler scale is a general scaling factor for how much the pitch varies due to doppler shifting in 3D sound. Doppler is the pitch bending effect when a sound comes towards the listener or moves away from it, much like the effect you hear when a train goes past you with its horn sounding. With dopplerscale you can exaggerate or diminish the effect.

Members.Name: DistanceFactor
Members.Summary: the relative distance factor, compared to 1.0 meters.

Members.Name: RolloffScale
Members.Summary: Setting this value makes the sound drop off faster or slower. The higher the value, the faster volume will attenuate, and conversely the lower the value, the slower it will attenuate. For example a rolloff factor of 1 will simulate the real world, where as a value of 2 will make sounds attenuate 2 times quicker.

Members.Name: SetCustomSortFunction
Members.Summary: When SortOrder is set to Custom, this lua function is used to determine the ordering of elements. Function should take two arguments (each will be an Instance child to compare), and return true if a comes before b, otherwise return false. In other words, use this function the same way you would use a table.sort function. The sorting should be deterministic, otherwise sort will fail and fall back to name order.

Members.Name: ApplyLayout
Members.Summary: Forces a relayout of all elements. Useful when sort is set to Custom.

Members.Name: SortOrder
Members.Summary: Determines how we decide which element to place next. Can be Name or Custom. If using Custom, make sure SetCustomSortFunction was called with an appropriate sort function.

Members.Name: FillDirection
Members.Summary: Determines which direction to fill the grid. Can be Horizontal or Vertical.

Members.Name: HorizontalAlignment
Members.Summary: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the x direction. Can be Left, Center, or Right.

Members.Name: VerticalAlignment
Members.Summary: Determines how grid is placed within it's parent's container in the y direction. Can be Top, Center, or Bottom.

Name: UIListLayout
Summary: Sets the position of UI elements in a list. You can use a UIListLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIListLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

Members.Name: Padding
Members.Summary: Determines the amount of free space between each element. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).

Name: UIGridLayout
Summary: Sets the position of UI elements in a 2D grid (this can be modified to 1D grid for list layout). This will also set the elements to a particular size, although this can be overridden with particular constraints on elements. You can use a UIGridLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIGridLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

Members.Name: CellSize
Members.Summary: Denotes what size each element should be. Can be overridden by elements using constraints on individual elements.

Members.Name: CellPadding
Members.Summary: How much space between elements there should be.

Members.Name: FillDirectionMaxCells
Members.Summary: Determines how many cells over in the FillDirection we go before starting a new row or column. Set to 0 for max cell count.  Will be clamped if this is set higher than the parent container allows room for.

Members.Name: AbsoluteSize
Members.Summary: Returns the current size of the grid. If more elements are added, this can increase. If elements are removed this can decrease.

Members.Name: StartCorner
Members.Summary: Which corner we start laying the elements out from. Can be TopLeft, TopRight, BottomLeft, BottomRight.

Name: UIPageLayout
Summary: Creates a paged viewing window, like the home screen of a mobile device. You can use a UIPageLayout by parenting it to a GuiObject. The UIPageLayout will then apply itself to all of its GuiObject siblings.

Members.Name: CurrentPage
Members.Summary: The page that is either currently being displayed or is the target of the current animation.

Members.Name: Circular
Members.Summary: Whether or not the page layout wraps around at the ends.

Members.Name: Padding
Members.Summary: Determines the amount that pages are separated from each other by. Can be set either using scale (Percentage of parent's size in the current direction) or offset (a static spacing value, similar to pixel size).

Members.Name: Animated
Members.Summary: Whether or not to animate transitions between pages.

Members.Name: EasingStyle
Members.Summary: The easing style to use when performing an animation.

Members.Name: EasingDirection
Members.Summary: The easing direction to use when performing an animation.

Members.Name: TweenTime
Members.Summary: The length of the animation.

Members.Name: Next
Members.Summary: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.

Members.Name: Previous
Members.Summary: Sets CurrentPage to the page after the current page and animates to it, or does nothing if there isn't a next page.

Members.Name: JumpTo
Members.Summary: If the instance is in the layout, then it sets CurrentPage to it and animtes to it. If circular layout is set, it will take the shortest path.

Members.Name: JumpToIndex
Members.Summary: If the index is >= 0 and less than the size of the layout, acts like JumpTo. If it's out of bounds and circular is set, it will animate the full distance between the in-bounds index of CurrentPage and the new index.

Members.Name: PageEnter

Name: ContextActionService
Summary: A service used to bind input to various lua functions.

Members.Name: BindAction
Members.Summary: Binds 'functionToBind' to fire when any 'inputTypes' happen. InputTypes can be variable in number and type. Types can be Enum.KeyCode, single character strings corresponding to keys, or Enum.UserInputType. 'actionName' is a key used by many other ContextActionService functions to query state. 'createTouchButton' if true will create a button on screen on touch devices.  This button will fire 'functionToBind' with three arguments: first argument is the actionName, second argument is the UserInputState of the input, and the third is the InputObject that fired this function. If 'functionToBind' yields or returns nil or Enum.ContextActionResult.Sink, the input will be sunk. If it returns Enum.ContextActionResult.Pass, the next bound action in the stack will be invoked.

Members.Name: SetTitle
Members.Summary: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'title' is set as the title of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether title will be set when button is manipulated.

Members.Name: SetDescription
Members.Summary: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'description' is set as the description of the bound action. This description will appear for users in a listing of current actions availables.

Members.Name: SetImage
Members.Summary: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'image' is set as the image of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether image will be set when button is manipulated.

Members.Name: SetPosition
Members.Summary: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then 'position' is set as the position of the touch button. Does nothing if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether position will be set when button is manipulated.

Members.Name: UnbindAction
Members.Summary: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, removes function from being called by all input that it was bound by (if function was also bound by a different action name as well, those bound input are still active). Will also remove any touch button created (if button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up).

Members.Name: UnbindAllActions
Members.Summary: Removes all functions bound. No actionNames will remain. All touch buttons will be removed. If button was manipulated manually there is no guarantee it will be cleaned up.

Members.Name: GetBoundActionInfo
Members.Summary: Returns a table with info regarding the function bound with 'actionName'. Table has the keys 'title' (current title that was set with SetTitle) 'image' (image set with SetImage) 'description' (description set with SetDescription) 'inputTypes' (tuple containing all input bound for this 'actionName') 'createTouchButton' (whether or not we created a touch button for this 'actionName').

Members.Name: GetAllBoundActionInfo
Members.Summary: Returns a table with all bound action info. Each entry is a key with 'actionName' and value being the same table you would get from ContextActionService:GetBoundActionInfo('actionName').

Members.Name: GetButton
Members.Summary: If 'actionName' key contains a bound action, then this will return the touch button (if was created). Returns nil if a touch button was not created. No guarantees are made whether button will be retrievable when button is manipulated.

Name: PointsService
Summary: A service used to query and award points for Roblox users using the universal point system.

Members.Name: PointsAwarded
Members.Summary: Fired when points are successfully awarded 'userId'. Also returns the updated balance of points for usedId in universe via 'userBalanceInUniverse', total points via 'userTotalBalance', and the amount points that were awarded via 'pointsAwarded'. This event fires on the server and also all clients in the game that awarded the points.

Members.Name: AwardPoints
Members.Summary: Will attempt to award the 'amount' points to 'userId', returns 'userId' awarded to, the number of points awarded, the new point total the user has in the game, and the total number of points the user now has. Will also fire PointsService.PointsAwarded. Works with server scripts ONLY.

Members.Name: GetPointBalance
Members.Summary: Returns the overall balance of points that player with userId has (the sum of all points across all games). Works with server scripts ONLY.

Members.Name: GetGamePointBalance
Members.Summary: Returns the balance of points that player with userId has in the current game (all placeID points combined within the game). Works with server scripts ONLY.

Members.Name: GetAwardablePoints
Members.Summary: Returns the number of points the current universe can award to players. Works with server scripts ONLY.

Members.Name: PromptPurchase
Members.Summary: Will prompt 'player' to purchase the item associated with 'assetId'.  'equipIfPurchased' is an optional argument that will give the item to the player immediately if they buy it (only applies to gear).  'currencyType' is also optional and will attempt to prompt the user with a specified currency if the product can be purchased with this currency, otherwise we use the default currency of the product.

Members.Name: GetProductInfo
Members.Summary: Takes one argument "assetId" which should be a number of an asset on www.roblox.com.  Returns a table containing the product information (if this process fails, returns an empty table).

Members.Name: PlayerOwnsAsset
Members.Summary: Checks to see if 'Player' owns the product associated with 'assetId'. Returns true if the player owns it, false otherwise. This call will produce a warning if called on a guest player.

Members.Name: ProcessReceipt
Members.Summary:
Callback that is executed for pending Developer Product receipts.
            
            If this function does not return Enum.ProductPurchaseDecision.PurchaseGranted, then you will not be granted the money for the purchase!
            
            The callback will be invoked with a table, containing the following informational fields:
            PlayerId - the id of the player making the purchase.
            PlaceIdWherePurchased - the specific place where the purchase was made.
            PurchaseId - a unique identifier for the purchase, should be used to prevent granting an item multiple times for one purchase.
            ProductId - the id of the purchased product.
            CurrencyType - the type of currency used (Tix, Robux).
            CurrencySpent - the amount of currency spent on the product for this purchase.

Members.Name: PromptPurchaseFinished
Members.Summary: Fired when a 'player' dismisses a purchase dialog for 'assetId'.  If the player purchased the item 'isPurchased' will be true, otherwise it will be false. This call will produce a warning if called on a guest player.

Members.Name: TouchEnabled
Members.Summary: Returns true if the local device accepts touch input, false otherwise.

Members.Name: KeyboardEnabled
Members.Summary: Returns true if the local device accepts keyboard input, false otherwise.

Members.Name: TouchTap
Members.Summary: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchPinch
Members.Summary: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchSwipe
Members.Summary: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchLongPress
Members.Summary: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchRotate
Members.Summary: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchPan
Members.Summary: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchStarted
Members.Summary: Fired when a user places their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchMoved
Members.Summary: Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchEnded
Members.Summary: Fired when a user moves their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touch' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: InputBegan
Members.Summary: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). Members.Name: InputChanged
Members.Summary: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). Members.Summary: Fired when a user moves a device that has an accelerometer. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: DeviceGravityChanged
Members.Summary: Fired when the force of gravity changes on a device that has an accelerometer. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: DeviceRotationChanged
Members.Summary: Fired when a user rotates a device that has an gyroscope. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Gyroscope, and position that shows total rotation in each local device axis.  The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. A second argument of Vector4 is the device's current quaternion rotation in reference to it's default reference frame. This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: GetDeviceAcceleration
Members.Summary: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current acceleration. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis.  The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: GetDeviceGravity
Members.Summary: Returns an InputObject that describes the device's current gravity vector. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Accelerometer, and position that shows the g force in each local device axis. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: GetDeviceRotation
Members.Summary: Returns an InputObject and a Vector4 that describes the device's current rotation vector. This is fired with an InputObject, which has type Enum.InputType.Gyroscope, and position that shows total rotation in each local device axis. The delta property describes the amount of rotation that last happened. The Vector4 is the device's current quaternion rotation in reference to it's default reference frame. This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: GetGlobalDataStore
Members.Summary: Returns the default data store

Members.Name: GetOrderedDataStore
Members.Summary: Returns an ordered data store with the given name and scope

Name: GlobalDataStore
Summary: Exposes functions for saving and loading data for the DataStoreService

Members.Name: OnUpdate
Members.Summary: Sets callback as a function to be executed any time the value associated with key is changed. It is important to disconnect the connection when the subscription to the key is no longer needed.

Members.Name: GetAsync
Members.Summary: Returns the value of the entry in the DataStore with the given key

Members.Name: IncrementAsync
Members.Summary: Increments the value of a particular key amd returns the incremented value

Members.Name: SetAsync
Members.Summary: Sets the value of the key. This overwrites any existing data stored in the key

Members.Name: UpdateAsync
Members.Summary: Retrieves the value of the key from the website, and updates it with a new value. The callback until the value fetched matches the value on the web. Returning nil means it will not save.

Name: OrderedDataStore
Summary: A type of DataStore where values must be positive integers. This makes OrderedDataStore suitable for leaderboard related scripting where you are required to order large amounts of data efficiently.

Members.Name: GetSortedAsync
Members.Summary: Returns a DataStorePages object. The length of each page is determined by pageSize, and the order is determined by isAscending. minValue and maxValue are optional parameters which will filter the result.

Members.Name: CameraSubject
Members.Summary: Where the Camera's focus is.  Any rotation of the camera will be about this subject.

Members.Name: CameraType
Members.Summary: Defines how the camera will behave. More info

Members.Name: CoordinateFrame
Members.Summary: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.

Members.Name: CFrame
Members.Summary: The current position and rotation of the Camera.  For most CameraTypes, the rotation is set such that the CoordinateFrame lookVector is pointing at the Focus.

Members.Name: FieldOfView
Members.Summary: The current angle, or width, of what the camera can see.  Current acceptable values are from 20 degrees to 80.

Members.Name: Focus
Members.Summary: The current CoordinateFrame that the camera is looking at.  Note: it is not always guaranteed that the camera is always looking here.

Members.Name: ViewportSize
Members.Summary: Holds the x,y screen resolution of the viewport the camera is presenting (note: this can differ from the AbsoluteSize property of a full screen gui).

Members.Name: GetRoll
Members.Summary: Returns the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.

Members.Name: WorldToScreenPoint
Members.Summary: Takes a 3D position in the world and projects it onto x,y coordinates of screen space. Returns two values, first is a Vector3 that has x,y position and z position which is distance from camera (negative if behind camera, positive if in front). Second return value is a boolean indicating if the first argument is an on-screen coordinate.

Members.Name: ScreenPointToRay
Members.Summary: Takes a 2D screen position and produces a Ray object to be used for 3D raycasting. Input is x,y screen coordinates, and a (optional, defaults to 0) z position which sets how far in the camera look vector to start the ray origin.

Members.Name: ViewportPointToRay
Members.Summary: Same as ScreenPointToRay, except no GUI offsets are taken into account. Useful for things like casting a ray from the middle of the Camera.ViewportSize

Members.Name: WorldToViewportPoint
Members.Summary: Same as WorldToScreenPoint, except no GUI offsets are taken into account.

Members.Name: SetRoll
Members.Summary: Sets the camera's current roll. Roll is defined in radians, and is stored as the delta from the camera's y axis default normal vector.

Members.Name: CharacterAutoLoads
Members.Summary: Set to true, when a player joins a game, they get a character automatically, as well as when they die.  When set to false, characters do not auto load and will only load in using Player:LoadCharacter().

Members.Name: players
Members.Summary: Use GetPlayers() instead

Name: ReplicatedStorage
Summary: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients and the server.

Name: ReplicatedFirst
Summary: A container whose contents are replicated to all clients (but not back to the server) first before anything else. Useful for creating loading guis, tutorials, etc.

Members.Name: RemoveRobloxLoadingScreen
Members.Summary: Removes the default Roblox loading screen from view. Call this when you are ready to either show your own loading gui, or when the game is ready to play.

Name: ServerStorage
Summary: A container whose contents are only on the server.

Name: ServerScriptService
Summary: A container whose contents should be scripts. Scripts that are added to the container are run on the server.

Name: Lighting
Summary: Responsible for all lighting aspects of the world (affects how things are rendered).

Members.Name: GetMinutesAfterMidnight
Members.Summary: The number of minutes that the current time is past midnight.  If currently at midnight, returns 0.  Will return decimal values if not at an exact minute.

Members.Name: GetMoonDirection
Members.Summary: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the moon. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the moon.

Members.Name: GetMoonPhase
Members.Summary: Currently always returns 0.75. MoonPhase cannot be edited.

Members.Name: GetSunDirection
Members.Summary: Returns the lookVector (Vector3) of the sun. If this lookVector was used in a CFrame, the Part would face the sun.

Members.Name: SetMinutesAfterMidnight
Members.Summary: Sets the time to be a certain number of minutes after midnight.  This works with integer and decimal values.

Members.Name: Ambient
Members.Summary: The hue of the global lighting.  Changing this changes the color tint of all objects in the Workspace.

Members.Name: Brightness
Members.Summary: How much global light each Part in the Workspace receives. Standard range is 0 to 1 (0 being little light), but can be increased all the way to 5 (colors start to be appear very different at this value).

Members.Name: ColorShift_Bottom
Members.Summary: The hue of global lighting on the bottom surfaces of an object.

Members.Name: ColorShift_Top
Members.Summary: The hue of global lighting on the top surfaces of an object.

Members.Name: FogColor
Members.Summary: A Color3 value that changes the hue of distance fog.

Members.Name: FogEnd
Members.Summary: The distance at which fog completely blocks your vision. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs

Members.Name: FogStart
Members.Summary: The distance at which the fog gradient begins. This distance is relative to the camera position. Units are in studs.

Members.Name: GeographicLatitude
Members.Summary: The latitude position the level is placed at. This affects sun position. More info

Members.Name: GlobalShadows
Members.Summary: Flag enabling shadows from sun and moon in the place

Members.Name: OutdoorAmbient
Members.Summary: Effective ambient value for outdoors, effectively shadow color outdoors (requires GlobalShadows enabled)

Members.Name: Outlines
Members.Summary: Flag enabling or disabling outlines on parts and terrain

Members.Name: ShadowColor
Members.Summary: Color the shadows appear as. Shadows are drawn mostly for characters, but depending on the lighting will also show for Parts in the Workspace.  Rendering settings can also affect if shadows are drawn.

Members.Name: TimeOfDay
Members.Summary: A string that represent the current time of day. Time is in 24-hour clock format "XX::YY:ZZ", where X is hour, Y is minute, and Z is seconds.

Members.Name: LightingChanged
Members.Summary: Fired whenever a property of Lighting is changed, or a skybox is added or removed. Skyboxes are of type 'Sky' and should be parented directly to lighting.

Name: Debris
Summary: A service that provides utility in cleaning up objects

Members.Name: addItem
Members.Summary: Use AddItem() instead

Members.Name: AddItem
Members.Summary: Adds an Instance into the debris service that will later be destroyed.  Second argument 'lifetime' is optional and specifies how long (in seconds) to wait before destroying the item. If no time is specified then the item added will automatically be destroyed in 10 seconds.

Members.Name: MaxItems
Members.Summary: Deprecated. No replacement

Members.Name: CameraMode
Members.Summary: An enum that describes how a Player's camera is allowed to behave. More info.

Members.Name: DataReady
Members.Summary: Read-only. If true, this Player's persistent data can be loaded, false otherwise. Info on Data Persistence.

Members.Name: LoadCharacter
Members.Summary: Loads in a new character for this player.  This will replace the player's current character, if they have one. This should be used in conjunction with Players.CharacterAutoLoads to control spawning of characters. This function only works from a server-side script (NOT a LocalScript).

Members.Name: playerFromCharacter
Members.Summary: Use GetPlayerFromCharacter() instead

Members.Name: WaitForDataReady
Members.Summary: Yields until the persistent data for this Player is ready to be loaded. Info on Data Persistence.

Members.Name: Idled
Members.Summary: Fired periodically after the user has been AFK for a while.  Currently this event is only fired for the *local* Player.  "time" is the time in seconds that the user has been idle.

Members.Name: FindPartsInRegion3
Members.Summary: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less

Members.Name: FindPartsInRegion3WithIgnoreList
Members.Summary: Returns parts in the area defined by the Region3, up to specified maxCount or 100, whichever is less

Members.Name: FindPartOnRay
Members.Summary: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)

Members.Name: FindPartOnRayWithIgnoreList
Members.Summary: Return type is (BasePart, Vector3) if the ray hits.  If it misses it will return (nil, PointAtEndOfRay)

Members.Name: PGSPhysicsSolverEnabled
Members.Summary: Boolean used to enable the experimental physics solver

Members.Name: FallenPartsDestroyHeight
Members.Summary: Sets the height at which falling characters and parts are destroyed. This property is not scriptable and can only be set in Studio

Name: BasePart
Summary: A structural class, not creatable

Members.Name: Color
Members.Summary: Color3 of the part.

Members.Name: CFrame
Members.Summary: Contains information regarding the Part's position and a matrix that defines the Part's rotation. Can read/write. More info

Members.Name: CanCollide
Members.Summary: Determines whether physical interactions with other Parts are respected.  If true, will collide and react with physics to other Parts.  If false, other parts will pass thru instead of colliding

Members.Name: Anchored
Members.Summary: Determines whether or not physics acts upon the Part.  If true, part stays 'Anchored' in space, not moving regardless of any collision/forces acting upon it.  If false, physics works normally on the part.

Members.Name: Elasticity
Members.Summary: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will rebound against another. a value of 1 is like a superball, and 0 is like a lead block.

Members.Name: Friction
Members.Summary: A float value ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f. Sets how much the Part will be able to slide. a value of 1 is no sliding, and 0 is no friction, so infinite sliding.

Members.Name: Locked
Members.Summary: Determines whether building tools (in-game and studio) can manipulate this Part.  If true, no editing allowed.  If false, editing is allowed.

Members.Name: Material
Members.Summary: Specifies the look and feel the Part should have. Note: this does not define the color the Part is, see BrickColor for that. More info

Members.Name: Reflectance
Members.Summary: Specifies how shiny the Part is. A value of 1 is completely reflective (chrome), while a value of 0 is no reflectance (concrete wall)

Members.Name: ResizeIncrement
Members.Summary: Sets the value for the smallest change in size allowable by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.

Members.Name: ResizeableFaces
Members.Summary: Sets the value for the faces allowed to be resized by the Resize(NormalId, int) function.

Members.Name: Transparency
Members.Summary: Sets how visible an object is. A value of 1 makes the object invisible, while a value of 0 makes the object opaque.

Members.Name: Velocity
Members.Summary: How fast the Part is traveling in studs/second. This property is NOT recommended to be modified directly, unless there is good reason.  Otherwise, try using a BodyForce to move a Part.

Members.Name: PositionLocal
Members.Summary: Position relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.

Members.Name: OrientationLocal
Members.Summary: Orientation relative to parent part, or global space if there is no parent.

Members.Name: Orientation
Members.Summary: Rotation around X, Y, and Z axis.  Rotations applied in YXZ order.

Members.Name: makeJoints
Members.Summary: Use MakeJoints() instead

Members.Name: MakeJoints
Members.Summary: Creates the appropriate SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model). This uses the SurfaceTypes defined on the surfaces of parts to create the appropriate welds. More info

Members.Name: BreakJoints
Members.Summary: Destroys SurfaceJoints with all parts that are touching this Instance (including internal joints in the Instance, as in a Model).

Members.Name: GetMass
Members.Summary: Returns a number that is the mass of this Instance.  Mass of a Part is immutable, and is changed only by the size of the Part.

Members.Name: Resize
Members.Summary: Resizes a Part in the direction of the face defined by 'NormalId', by the amount specified by 'deltaAmount'. If the operation will expand the part to intersect another Instance, the part will not resize at all.  Return true if the call is successful, false otherwise.

Members.Name: getMass
Members.Summary: Use GetMass() instead

Members.Name: LocalSimulationTouched
Members.Summary: Deprecated. Use Touched instead

Members.Name: StoppedTouching
Members.Summary: Deprecated. Use TouchEnded instead

Members.Name: TouchEnded
Members.Summary: Fired when the part stops touching another part

Name: GuiMain
Summary: Deprecated, please use ScreenGui

Name: LayerCollector
Summary: The base class of ScreenGui, BillboardGui, and SurfaceGui.

Name: ScreenGui
Summary: The core GUI object on which tools are built.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered as a 2D overlay

Name: FunctionalTest
Summary: Deprecated. Use TestService instead

Name: BillboardGui
Summary: A GUI that adorns an object in the 3D world.  Add Frames/Labels/Buttons to this object to have them rendered while attached to a 3D object

Members.Name: Adornee
Members.Summary: The Object the billboard gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.

Members.Name: AbsolutePosition
Members.Summary: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.

Members.Name: AbsoluteSize
Members.Summary: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.

Members.Name: Active
Members.Summary: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

Members.Name: AlwaysOnTop
Members.Summary: If true, billboard gui does not get occluded by 3D objects, but always renders on the screen.

Members.Name: Enabled
Members.Summary: If true, billboard gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.

Members.Name: ExtentsOffset
Members.Summary: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the extents of the 3d object it is rendering from.

Members.Name: PlayerToHideFrom
Members.Summary: Specifies a Player that the BillboardGui will not render to.

Members.Name: StudsOffset
Members.Summary: A Vector3 (x,y,z) defined in studs that will offset the gui from the centroid of the 3d object it is rendering from

Members.Name: SizeOffset
Members.Summary: A Vector2 (x,y) defined in studs that will offset the gui size from it's current size.

Members.Name: Size
Members.Summary: A UDim2 value describing the size of the BillboardGui. More information on UDim2 is available here. Relative values are defined as one-to-one with studs.

Members.Name: LightInfluence
Members.Summary: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the billboard gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

Name: SurfaceGui
Summary: Renders its contained GuiObjects flat against the face of a part.

Members.Name: Adornee
Members.Summary: The Object the surface gui uses as its base to render from.  Currently, the only way to set this property is thru a script, and must exist in the workspace.  This will only render if the object assigned derives from BasePart.

Members.Name: Active
Members.Summary: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

Members.Name: Enabled
Members.Summary: If true, surface gui will render, otherwise rendering will be skipped.

Members.Name: LightInfluence
Members.Summary: Specifies the amount of influence lighting has on the surface gui. A value of 0 is unlit, 1 is fully lit. Fractional values blend from unlit to lit.

Members.Name: AbsolutePosition
Members.Summary: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current position (x,y) in pixel space, from the top left corner of the GuiObject.

Members.Name: AbsoluteSize
Members.Summary: A read-only Vector2 value that is the GuiObject's current size (width, height) in pixel space.

Name: InputObject
Summary: An object that describes a particular user input, such as mouse movement, touches, keyboard, and more.

Members.Name: UserInputType
Members.Summary: An enum that describes what kind of input this object is describing (mousebutton, touch, etc.).  See Enum.UserInputType for more info.

Members.Name: UserInputState
Members.Summary: An enum that describes what state of a particular input (touch began, touch moved, touch ended, etc.). See Enum.UserInputState for more info.

Members.Name: Position
Members.Summary: A Vector3 value that describes a positional value of this input. For mouse and touch input, this is the screen position of the mouse/touch, described in the x and y components. For mouse wheel input, the z component describes whether the wheel was moved forward or backward.

Members.Name: KeyCode
Members.Summary: An enum that describes what kind of input is being pressed. For types of input like Keyboard, this describes what key was pressed. For input like mousebutton, this provides no additional information.

Members.Name: TweenPosition
Members.Summary: Smoothly moves a GuiObject from its current position to 'endPosition'. The only required argument is 'endPosition'. More info

Members.Name: TweenSize
Members.Summary: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize'. The only required argument is 'endSize'. More info

Members.Name: TweenSizeAndPosition
Members.Summary: Smoothly translates a GuiObject's current size to 'endSize', and also smoothly translates the GuiObject's current position to 'endPosition'. The only required arguments are 'endSize' and 'endPosition'. More info

Members.Name: Active
Members.Summary: If true, this GuiObject can fire mouse events and will pass them to any GuiObjects layered underneath, while false will do neither.

Members.Name: BackgroundColor3
Members.Summary: A Color3 value that specifies the background color for the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

Members.Name: BackgroundTransparency
Members.Summary: A number value that specifies how transparent the background of the GuiObject is. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

Members.Name: BorderColor3
Members.Summary: A Color3 value that specifies the color of the outline of the GuiObject. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

Members.Name: BorderSizePixel
Members.Summary: A number value that specifies the thickness (in pixels) of the outline of the GuiObject. Currently this value can only be set to either 0 or 1, any other number has no effect. This value is ignored if the Style property (not found on all GuiObjects) is set to something besides custom.

Members.Name: ClipsDescendants
Members.Summary: If set to true, any descendants of this GuiObject will only render if contained within it's borders. If set to false, all descendants will render regardless of position.

Members.Name: Draggable
Members.Summary: If true, allows a GuiObject to be dragged by the user's mouse. The events 'DragBegin' and 'DragStopped' are fired when the appropriate action happens, and only will fire on Draggable=true GuiObjects.

Members.Name: Size
Members.Summary: A UDim2 value describing the size of the GuiObject on screen in both absolute and relative coordinates. More information on UDim2 is available here.

Members.Name: Position
Members.Summary: A UDim2 value describing the position of the top-left corner of the GuiObject on screen. More information on UDim2 is available here.

Members.Name: SizeConstraint
Members.Summary: The direction(s) that an object can be resized in. More info.

Members.Name: ZIndex
Members.Summary: Describes the ordering in which overlapping GuiObjects will be drawn. A value of 1 is drawn first, while higher values are drawn in ascending order (each value draws over the last).

Members.Name: BackgroundColor
Members.Summary: Deprecated. Use BackgroundColor3 instead

Members.Name: BorderColor
Members.Summary: Deprecated. Use BorderColor3 instead

Members.Name: SelectionImageObject
Members.Summary: Overrides the default selection adornment (used for gamepads). For best results, this should point to a GuiObject.

Members.Name: DragBegin
Members.Summary: Fired when a GuiObject with Draggable set to true starts to be dragged. 'InitialPosition' is a UDim2 value of the position of the GuiObject before any drag operation began.

Members.Name: DragStopped
Members.Summary: Always fired after a DragBegin event, DragStopped is fired when the user releases the mouse button causing a drag operation on the GuiObject. Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the top-left absolute position of the GuiObject when the event is fired.

Members.Name: MouseEnter
Members.Summary: Fired when the mouse enters a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

Members.Name: MouseLeave
Members.Summary: Fired when the mouse leaves a GuiObject, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

Members.Name: MouseMoved
Members.Summary: Fired when the mouse is inside a GuiObject and moves, as long as the GuiObject is active (see active property for more detail). Arguments 'x', and 'y' specify the absolute pixel position of the mouse.

Members.Name: TouchTap
Members.Summary: Fired when a user taps their finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the tap gesture. This event only fires locally.  This event will always fire regardless of game state.

Members.Name: TouchPinch
Members.Summary: Fired when a user pinches their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the pinch gesture. 'scale' is a float that indicates the difference from the beginning of the pinch gesture. 'velocity' is a float indicating how quickly the pinch gesture is happening. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: TouchSwipe
Members.Summary: Fired when a user swipes their fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'swipeDirection' is an Enum.SwipeDirection, indicating the direction the user swiped. 'numberOfTouches' is an int that indicates how many touches were involved with the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: TouchLongPress
Members.Summary: Fired when a user holds at least one finger for a short amount of time on the same screen position on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: TouchRotate
Members.Summary: Fired when a user rotates two fingers on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'rotation' is a float indicating how much the rotation has gone from the start of the gesture. 'velocity' is a float that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.  This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: TouchPan
Members.Summary: Fired when a user drags at least one finger on a TouchEnabled device. 'touchPositions' is a Lua array of Vector2, each indicating the position of all the fingers involved in the gesture. 'totalTranslation' is a Vector2, indicating how far the pan gesture has gone from its starting point. 'velocity' is a Vector2 that indicates how quickly the gesture is being performed in each dimension. 'state' indicates the Enum.UserInputState of the gesture.

Members.Name: InputBegan
Members.Summary: Fired when a user begins interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button down, touch begin, keyboard button down, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: InputChanged
Members.Summary: Fired when a user changes interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse move, touch move, mouse wheel, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

Members.Name: InputEnded
Members.Summary: Fired when a user stops interacting via a Human-Computer Interface device (Mouse button up, touch end, keyboard button up, etc.). 'inputObject' is an InputObject, which contains useful data for querying user input.  This event only fires locally.

Name: Frame
Summary: A container object used to layout other GUI objects

Members.Name: Style
Members.Summary: Determines how a frame will look. Uses Enum.FrameStyle. More info

Name: ScrollingFrame
Summary: A container object used to layout other GUI objects, and allows for scrolling.

Members.Name: ScrollingEnabled
Members.Summary: Determines whether or not scrolling is allowed on this frame. If turned off, no scroll bars will be rendered.

Members.Name: CanvasSize
Members.Summary: Determines the size of the area that is scrollable. The UDim2 is calculated using the parent gui's size, similar to the regular Size property on gui objects.

Members.Name: CanvasPosition
Members.Summary: The absolute position the scroll frame is in respect to the canvas size. The minimum this can be set to is (0,0), while the max is the absolute canvas size - AbsoluteWindowSize.

Members.Name: AbsoluteWindowSize
Members.Summary: The size in pixels of the frame, without the scrollbars.

Members.Name: ScrollBarThickness
Members.Summary: How thick the scroll bar appears. This applies to both the horizontal and vertical scroll bars. Can be set to 0 for no bars render.

Members.Name: TopImage
Members.Summary: The "Up" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "left" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

Members.Name: MidImage
Members.Summary: The "Middle" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this can vary in the y direction, but is always set at ScrollBarThickness in x direction. This is also used as the "mid" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

Members.Name: BottomImage
Members.Summary: The "Down" image on the vertical scrollbar. Size of this is always ScrollBarThickness by ScrollBarThickness. This is also used as the "right" image on the horizontal scroll bar.

Name: ImageLabel
Summary: A GUI object containing an Image

Members.Name: Image
Members.Summary: Specifies the id of the texture to display. More info

Members.Name: ScaleType
Members.Summary: Specifies how an image should be displayed. See ScaleType for more info.

Members.Name: SliceCenter
Members.Summary: If ScaleType is set to Slice, this Rect is used to specify the central part of the image. Everything outside of this is considered to be the border.

Members.Name: TileSize
Members.Summary: If ScaleType is set to Tile, this sets the size of the tile.

Name: GuiButton

Members.Name: AutoButtonColor

Members.Name: Modal

Members.Name: MouseButton1Click
